  "informal_statement": "Another assembly piece toward the integer_isGoodPair_iff characterization for Erdos Problem #349: for integer t >= 2 and any integer alpha, the pair (t, alpha) is NOT good -- it is false that eventually every integer k is a finite sum of distinct elements of the range of n |-> floor(t*alpha^n). This is a sublemma supporting the integer_isGoodPair_iff characterization, not a resolution of #349 itself (which asks, in general, for which real t, alpha the sequence floor(t*alpha^n) is additively complete -- still genuinely OPEN).",
  "informal_proof_idea": "Pick k not divisible by t (e.g. k = t*(|N|+1) + 1 for any threshold N). Then k cannot equal any finite subset-sum, since every term t*alpha^n is a multiple of t (as t, alpha are both integers), so any such sum would be divisible by t, but k is not -- contradicting eventual representability.",
  "formal_statement_pp": "theorem erdos_349_int_coeff_ge_two_not_is_good_pair : ∀ (t : ℤ), 2 ≤ t → ∀ (α : ℤ), ¬ (∀ᶠ k in Filter.atTop, k ∈ {n : ℤ | ∃ B : Finset ℤ, ↑B ⊆ Set.range (fun n : ℕ ↦ ⌊(t:ℝ) * (α:ℝ) ^ n⌋) ∧ n = ∑ i ∈ B, i})",
  "proof_body_path": "lean/MathCorpus/Frontier/Erdos/Erdos349IntCoeffGeTwoNotIsGoodPair.lean",
